<title>AUSTRALIA: BHP says may cut 500 Magma Copper jobs.</title>
<headline>BHP says may cut 500 Magma Copper jobs.</headline>
<dateline>MELBOURNE 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Broken Hill Pty Co Ltd on Friday confirmed up to 500 jobs may be cut from the San Manuel division of its Arizona-based Magma Copper Co unit as part of its effort to increase productivity in its copper business.</p>
<p>The possibility of the job losses was &quot;broadly consistent&quot; with a review underway at BHP to improve its copper business, BHP spokesman Murray Hohnen told Reuters. The Australian nespaper reported on Friday that the job cuts represented a first step in a fundamental restructure of the Magma assets, acquired by BHP in December 1995 for A$3.2 billion.</p>
